<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.2. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Overview</h2>
<p>
    This page documents the Exception Service Type intake flow in R4C (Return for Credit): how an Agent logs in,
    creates an Exception case, adds and validates line items, and moves the case through to completion. Exception
    supports two Remedy paths, Credit and NPR-Credit, which follow different Line Items flows.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Purpose:</strong> Give Developers and QA a single, accurate reference for the Exception intake case
    lifecycle, including case creation, request header and collection details, the Credit vs. NPR-Credit line item
    flows (search/upload, PO history, product validation, credit price validation, and, for NPR-Credit, Warranty
    Entitlement Check), case view/edit behavior, and the CPN Indicator check.
</p>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.3. ">Pre-Requisites</h2>
<p>To login as an agent, we should have Sandbox access for the required test environment. We have two types of Agents L1
    &amp; L2. L1 Agent can login to the Sandbox URL and create a Return Request for Stock Rotation. L2 Agent can view
    the cases assigned to them and can change the case owner. This page will only pertain to L1 agent.</p>
<p>
    <strong>Sandbox (IAOQA) Link :</strong> <a
        href="https://isvc--isvciaoqa.sandbox.my.salesforce.com/">https://isvc--isvciaoqa.sandbox.my.salesforce.com/</a>
</p>
<p>Access related issues, Contact: @Indus ISVC GRL R4C  </p>
