<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.6. ">SAP Blocks scenarios</h2>
<p>
    Before a Sold To, Payer or Ship To can be used on a case, R4C checks Export Compliance, Order, Billing and
    Delivery blocks at CMF and Sales Area level. Block values, hard-stop behavior, and how Case creation differs
    from Case edit are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Block Scenarios" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for the block rules.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Exception Intake:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Case creation: any Sold To CMF, Sales Area or Ship To CMF/Sales Area with a hard block is excluded from its
        respective selection dropdown; a Payer-level block surfaces as an error toast on Sold To selection.</li>
    <li>Case edit: a hard block present at Sold To CMF, Sales Area, Payer or Ship To level blocks the Edit action
        with an error toast.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.7. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Request Header Details</h2>
<ul>
    <li>User should fill in all the mandatory fields which are marked with the red color asterisk symbol (<span
            style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);">*</span>) and until all mandatory fields are
        entered, next button should be disabled.</li>
    <li>Contact Name &amp; Account Name will be auto populated as Hyperlinks. The selected Service Type is shown as the
        text field.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    Sold To/Ship To CMF resolution, wildcard search, and address auto-population rules are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Address &amp; Contact Management" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for that logic.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Exception Intake:</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Remedy:</strong> For Service type "Exception" the possible remedy values are 'Credit', 'NPR-Credit'.
        Agent can select one value from the dropdown.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Return Reason:</strong> These values are determined based on the selected 'Service Type' and 'Remedy'.
        Values are fetched from the 'Customer Return Reasons' object and displayed in dropdown for agent to choose from.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Return Reason Justification:</strong> This is a mandatory input text field where agent needs to fill the
        proper Reason/Justification for creating Exception Return case.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>CIRS Number:</strong> This is the input text where agent can enter duplicate CIRS number as well by
        using the format (<strong>CIxxxx-xxxx</strong>) where x is any number.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Description:</strong> Agent can provide the issue details in case notes field.
    </li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="c70f8594-daa8-4ad5-9de5-476bdfaed8c4" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
