<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.2. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Purchase/Sales Order Search</h3>
<p>
    The PO/SO search mechanics and PO History/Validate PO button flow are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Product Validation" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for that logic.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Exception Intake (Remedy = Credit):</p>
<ul>
    <li>On click of Search button, date range is automatically selected 5 years in the backend.</li>
    <li>Data is sent to 'ECA View via Orchestration layer' to get line items.</li>
    <li>Line items are validated using Item Type <strong>'FERT' or 'KITS'</strong>.</li>
    <li>Agent can select line items to proceed to 'Product Validation'; can see the "Delete Line item" column (removes
        the line in Case creation, unselects it in Case Edit).</li>
    <li>Users can proceed only with up to 999 lines; more than that shows "You can only proceed with 999 lines".</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.3. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Product Search</h3>
<p>
    The MM/CPN radio search mechanics, the Multiple CPN Scenario, and the PO History/Validate PO button flow are
    documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Product Validation" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for that logic.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Exception Intake (Remedy = Credit):</p>
<ul>
    <li>Line-item data is validated using Item Type <strong>'FERT' or 'KITS'</strong>.</li>
    <li>PO History validation is called via the <strong>POH API</strong>, with an initial date range of Current date
        &ndash; 5 years.</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.4. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Bulk Upload</h3>
<p>
    <span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);"> # add all the relevant
        validations for bulk upload </span>
</p>
<p>
    The CSV template/drag-drop/Validate mechanics are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Product Validation" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for that logic.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Exception Intake (Remedy = Credit):</p>
<ul>
    <li>Here for each line-item data entered, MM number or CPN number should be mandatorily entered along with Box
        Condition and Return quantity.</li>
    <li>If agent wants to specify 'Return Package Conditions', the acceptable values are 'Outer Box Opened -- Product
        Unsealed', 'Outer Box Opened -- Product sealed' and 'Box closed -- Factory sealed'. All other values would be
        invalid.</li>
    <li>The agent can upload only 750 lines per bulk upload. It is the maximum limit, and more than 750 lines cannot be
        uploaded at once. Since the case submission limit is 999 lines, the remaining 249 lines can be uploaded after
        the initial 750 lines are processed. <span
            style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);">#ISSUE</span>
    </li>
    <li>Uploading more than 750 lines through bulk upload will show an error message saying: "Please search/upload a
        file with a maximum of 750 lines only."</li>
    <li>Line-item data is re-validated using Item Type <strong>'FERT' or 'KITS'</strong>.</li>
    <li>PO History validation is called via the <strong>POH API</strong>, with an initial date range of Current date
        &ndash; 5 years.</li>
    <li>Users can proceed only with up to 999 lines; more than that shows "You can only proceed with 999 lines".</li>
</ul>
<p>
    The Disti Channel Product Status check mechanism and its IAO-flag/field split are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Product Validation" />
    </ac:link>
    . Exception Intake documents the following code list:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>The following Disti Channel Product Status Codes are allowed for Agent Case creation: <strong>AC, RS, EN, OB,
            RP, RT, QR, NO, E2</strong>
    </li>
    <li>The following Disti Channel Product Status Codes are 'not allowed' for Agent Case creation: <strong>PA,
            NI</strong>
    </li>
    <li>When we try to create a case with product status <strong>PA</strong> and <strong>NI</strong> it will be a
        Hardstop and will show an error message saying "Current status is PA" and for NI "current status is NI"</li>
    <li>If the Product status is not valid or empty (null), it will display an error message saying "No valid product
        status were found"</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="0bbb4a01-d9bd-4dee-96f1-e0c3ddc68ee9" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">NCNR Check and PO History matching apply here too</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            In addition to the Product Status check above, PO History for this Remedy also runs the NCNR (Non-
            Cancellable, Non-Returnable) checks and uses the same PO History matching rules (including the CPU
            Extended Warranty and VISID special cases, the VISID rejection status, and the PO-number-changed
            confirmation popup); see "NCNR Check", "NCNR Flag Check", and "How a line item is matched against the
            PO History response" under Product Validation/PO History in the NPR-Credit section below. None of these
            are specific to NPR-Credit.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="0bbb4a01-d9bd-4dee-96f1-e0c3ddc68ee8" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>On click of 'Next' button if Return Reason is 'Exception Return', Agent needs to select <strong>only one line
                item</strong> to proceed to further steps, else it is a hard stop to proceed further.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-11-27.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>If the agent is in Credit price step and wants to change the line item, he should deselect the current line item
        in step 2 and go back to the search page to add a new line item.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-11-40.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>If agent adds the new line item, then on click of next button, if the agent has not deselected the previous line
        item which is in step-2, he will be notified to clear the line items in step-2 first to proceed with adding the
        new one.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-11-53.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Note:</strong>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>If Return Reason is <strong>Exception return</strong> where Price can change, it can be changed to zero
        (<strong>0</strong>).</li>
    <li>If not Zero (<strong>0</strong>), Price should be the same which is fetched from <strong>PO price</strong> to
