<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.5. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Credit Price Validation</h3>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-12-23.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>In "Credit Price Validation" section, agent can see "Get Credit Price" button enabled for all selected line
        items.</li>
    <li>Enter the Return Quantity for each line item as it is a mandatory field. Return Po &amp; Debit Reference number
        are optional fields.</li>
    <li>If a line item has a ULT (Unique Life Time identifier), its Return Quantity is locked to 1 and the field is
        disabled. This rule is not Remedy-specific, so it applies here as well as under NPR-Credit's Warranty
        Entitlement Check.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="ad9e6d8c-f53d-416a-af55-e6e4249b716a" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Entry to this step is gated</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            Beyond the "select only one line item" rule already noted under Product Search, clicking Next also
            blocks with an "Existing Line Item" error if a previously selected line item (e.g. from a prior search
            or from Case Edit) is still present without being explicitly cleared. The agent must deselect it and
            return to the search page before a new line item can be added, as described at the end of this section.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
    <ac:image ac:width="906">
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-12-37.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Once agent clicks on 'Get Credit Price' button:<ul>
            <li>If the Distribution channel of the case that is being created is 01, or Return Reason is Exception
                Return or Quarterly Exception Return, then the Unit Price of the Line item is determined from the
                POH API response: the ContraRevenueAdjustmentRequestlineNetPriceAmt attribute value is used when
                present, falling back to the SalesOrderLineNetPriceAmt attribute value only when it isn't.</li>
            <li>If the Distribution channel is anything other than 01-Direct, i.e., 02-Industrial Distribution or
                03-Retail, then the Unit Price of every Line Item will be fetched by making a callout to PIC API by
                passing required Parameters (selected MMs, selected Sold to CMF and sales org).</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>'Net credit Value' of each valid line item is calculated as 'Return Quantity' * 'Credit Price' and is displayed
        in the 'Net credit value' column.</li>
    <li>If no credit price value is fetched from PIC API, then the agent has the option to enter the price and Reason in
        the input columns.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <strong>PIC System Price Zero Scenarios:</strong>
</p>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-12-51.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>The agent needs to fill in the 'Reason for the price change' field if he enters the credit price manually.</li>
    <li>Without filling out the Credit Price and Reason for price change, the agent can't proceed to the next step with
        that line-item; these validations will be checked on click of "Save and view summary" button.</li>
    <li>If the agent enters the credit price and Reason for price change for all required line-items.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="ad9e6d8c-f53d-416a-af55-e6e4249b716b" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Reason for Price Change: when it's required, and the zero-price rules</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            This field, and the related zero-price rules below, only apply to the Agent UI (the Portal doesn't
            enforce them). The 'Reason for Price Change' field becomes visible when Return Reason is Quarterly
            Exception, or when Return Reason is on either of two configured lists of eligible return reasons.
        </p>
        <p>
            Those two lists behave differently on "Save and View Summary":
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Return Reasons on the first list: the Credit Price must be exactly zero, or the agent is told to
                set the price to zero.</li>
            <li>Return Reasons on the second list: the Credit Price is exempted from the normal "must be greater
                than zero" check, so it can be left at zero or match the original PO price.</li>
            <li>Any other Return Reason: the Credit Price must be greater than zero, or the agent is told to fill
                in a valid Credit Price.</li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-13-3.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>This is a mandatory field to proceed further. Once the agent fills in the Reason for Price Change and clicks on
        Submit, the case will be created, and the user will be navigated to the View Summary page.</li>
    <li>Agent also has the option to select the 'Box Condition' of each line item.</li>
    <li>After successfully obtaining the credit price, the 'Save &amp; View Summary' button is enabled so the agent can
        move to the view page.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="ad9e6d8c-f53d-416a-af55-e6e4249b716f" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>Box Condition is <strong>mandatory</strong> for any line item whenever the case's Remedy is Credit, not
            only for Quarterly Exception or GRL Exception Return. It is also mandatory when Return Reason is 'Free
            of Charge Sample'. If left blank, the agent cannot proceed; this is checked on click of 'Save and View
            Summary' and the agent is notified by a toast message.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-13-20.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="fca54f18-999b-41b4-9dc6-ad2a10bb14f0" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>If Return Reason is Quarterly Exception, agent can always change the price which is fetched from the POH
            system.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
    <ac:image>
