<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.10.4. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Bulk Upload</h3>
<p>
    The CSV template/drag-drop/Validate mechanics are documented once in
    <ac:link>
        <ri:page ri:content-title="Product Validation" />
    </ac:link>
    &mdash; refer there for that logic.
</p>
<p>How this applies to Exception Intake (Remedy = NPR-Credit):</p>
<ul>
    <li>Here for each line-item data entered, MM number or CPN number should be mandatorily entered along with
        quantity (no Box Condition field for this Remedy).</li>
    <li>If agent wants to specify 'Return Package Conditions', the acceptable values are 'Outer Box Opened -- Product
        Unsealed' and 'Box closed -- Factory sealed'. All other values would be invalid. (Note: this is a shorter
        list than the Credit-remedy flow, which also allows 'Outer Box Opened -- Product sealed'.)</li>
    <li>The agent can upload only 750 lines per bulk upload. It is the maximum limit, and more than 750 lines cannot
        be uploaded at once. Since the case submission limit is 999 lines, the remaining 249 lines can be uploaded
        after the initial 750 lines are processed.</li>
    <li>Uploading more than 750 lines through bulk upload will show an error message saying: "Please search/upload a
        file with a maximum of 750 lines only."</li>
    <li>Line-item data is re-validated using Item Type <strong>'FERT' or 'KITS'</strong>.</li>
    <li>Agent can proceed by clicking 'Next' to the 'Warranty Entitlement' screen. As with Product Search above, PO
        History validation for bulk-uploaded lines is not called inline here &mdash; it happens later, in Product
        Validation/PO History below.</li>
    <li>Users can proceed only with up to 999 lines; more than that shows "You can only proceed with 999 lines".</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.10.5. ">Warranty Entitlement Check</h3>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-16-55.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Agent can enter the Product Unique Id for the line items in the UI.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-17-7.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>On click of 'Warranty entitlement check' button, we are checking <strong>Return Quantity Greater Than
            One</strong>
