<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.10.6. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Product Validation/PO History</h3>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-20-13.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<p>
    <strong>NCNR Check:</strong> Before the PO History callout runs, an NCNR (Non-Cancellable, Non-Returnable) check
    runs across all selected line items, controlled by the NCNR_Check setting. When enabled, it applies to Exception
    and Stock Rotation cases. For each selected line, the check looks up the 'NCNR Matrix' using that line's Product
    Status Code (<code>Sales_Issue_Channel_StatusCode_Numeric__c</code>) and Item Custom Indicator
    (<code>Item_Custom_Indicator__c</code>). A matrix record matches when both values match, or when one of the two
    fields is blank on the matrix record (a blank field acts as a wildcard for that field). If a matching NCNR
    matrix record is found, the line item is deselected and shown with the error "Record is NCNR".
</p>
<ul>
    <li>On click of the PO History Button, we will be performing a POH API callout to get the PO numbers by sending the
        parameters MMs, Active CMFs of the bag, Start date, End date, sales org, Disti channel</li>
    <li>While validating from POH API initially the data range would be Current date -- 5 years. </li>
    <li>If we get the PO numbers for all the required line items, agent can directly proceed further.</li>
    <li>If we don't get the PO numbers for all the selected line items, we will show an error toast message.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <strong>How a line item is matched against the PO History response:</strong> most line items are matched by MM
    number against the selected items. Two exceptions:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>If the line has a ULT with Warranty Type 'Extended Warranty' (CPU Extended Warranty), it is matched by MM
        number together with the Service Contract Number instead of the usual delivery-note match. This only
        applies in the IAO environment.</li>
    <li>If the line's ULT type is VISID, it is matched by MM number together with the Delivery Note Number
        (padded to 10 characters) instead.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <strong>VISID rejection status:</strong> If a VISID line item ends up in an error state after PO History
    processing, it is flagged and its line-item status is set to a distinct "CPU POH Rejection" status, separately
    from the ordinary Error state used for other failed lines.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>PO number changed confirmation:</strong> If PO History updates a line's PO number to something
    different from what the agent previously entered, a confirmation popup lists the MM number, the old PO number,
    and the new PO number for every affected line, once PO History processing finishes.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>NCNR Flag Check:</strong> Separately, the PO History response itself carries an NcnrFlag value for each
    line. In the IAO environment, if NcnrFlag is 'X' or 'Z', the line item is deselected and shown with the error
    "Product is non-cancellable and non-returnable" &mdash; this applies regardless of whether the line already
    passed the NCNR Matrix check above.
</p>
<ul>
    <li>We do an additional validation check after the PO history check is done; this is done for each line item
        individually.</li>
    <li>If every selected line item is already PO-validated when this step is reached (e.g. re-entering the step
        without changing the selection), the PO History callout is skipped entirely and processing goes straight to
        the NPR rule matrix check below.</li>
    <li>Using the line item details, we query the 'NPR rule matrix records' and if the corresponding matrix record is
        found, then the line item is validated.</li>
    <li>If the validation fails, the line item is disabled, and the customer is shown the validation error message 'This
        product is not eligible for this return reason'.</li>
    <li>Agent can proceed to the next step by clicking on 'Next'. Agent would be navigated to the 'Credit Price
        validation screen'.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-20-25.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="3ad2eb66-d8b6-4b60-a26f-925f33010718" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>PO History validation will be bypassed for the line items which are coming from PO Search and also line items
            validated under the Validate PO functionality.</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="3ad2eb66-d8b6-4b60-a26f-925f33010726" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>The NCNR Matrix Check and NCNR Flag Check described above are not specific to the NPR-Credit flow &mdash;
            they run whenever PO History runs for an Exception case, including the Credit-remedy flow (see Bulk
            Upload above).</p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.10.7. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Credit Price Validation</h3>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-20-41.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>In the "Credit Price Validation" step, agent can see the "Credit Price Validation" button enabled for all
        selected line items.</li>
    <li>Enter the Return Quantity for each line item as it is a mandatory field. Return Po &amp; Debit Reference number
        are optional fields.</li>
    <li>Once agent clicks on the 'Credit Price Validation' button:<ul>
            <li>If the Distribution channel of the case that is being created is 01, then the Unit Price of the Line
                item is determined from the POH API response: the ContraRevenueAdjustmentRequestlineNetPriceAmt
                attribute value is used when present, falling back to the SalesOrderLineNetPriceAmt attribute value
                only when it isn't.</li>
            <li>If the Distribution channel is anything apart from 01-Direct, then the Unit Price of every line item
                will be fetched by making a callout to PIC API by passing required parameters (selected MMs, selected
                Sold to CMF and sales org).<span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);"> #
                    review</span>
            </li>
            <li>If no credit price value is fetched from PIC API, then the agent has the option to enter the price and
                Reason in the input columns.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    <strong>PIC System Price Zero Scenarios:</strong>
</p>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-21-0.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>The agent needs to fill in the 'Reason for the price change' field if he enters the credit price manually. </li>
    <li>Without filling out the Credit Price and Reason for price change, the agent can't proceed to the next step with
        that line-item; these validations will be checked on click of "Save and view summary" button.</li>
    <li>If the agent enters the credit price and Reason for price change for all required line-items.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="ad9e6d8c-f53d-416a-af55-e6e4249b716c" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Reason for Price Change: when it's required, and the zero-price rules</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            This rule set is identical to the Credit-remedy flow above, and is not remedy-specific: this field, and
            the related zero-price rules below, only apply to the Agent UI (the Portal doesn't enforce them). The
            'Reason for Price Change' field becomes visible when Return Reason is Quarterly Exception, or when
            Return Reason is on either of two configured lists of eligible return reasons.
        </p>
        <p>
            Those two lists behave differently on "Save and View Summary":
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Return Reasons on the first list: the Credit Price must be exactly zero, or the agent is told to
                set the price to zero.</li>
            <li>Return Reasons on the second list: the Credit Price is exempted from the normal "must be greater
                than zero" check, so it can be left at zero or match the original PO price.</li>
            <li>Any other Return Reason: the Credit Price must be greater than zero, or the agent is told to fill
                in a valid Credit Price.</li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-21-15.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>This is a mandatory field to proceed further. Once the agent fills in the Reason for Price Change and clicks on
        Submit, the case will be created, and the user will be navigated to the View Summary page.</li>
    <li>'Net credit Value' of each valid line item is calculated as 'Return Quantity' * 'Credit Price' and displayed in
        the 'Net credit value' column.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-21-32.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>After successfully obtaining the credit price, the 'Save &amp; View Summary' button is enabled so the agent can
        move to the view page.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.11. ">View Summary Page</h2>
<ul>
    <li>On clicking the button, agent is navigated to the 'Save &amp; View summary'/'Ready to Submit' page.</li>
    <li>Here agent can see all the case details briefly and confirm if everything is correct before he can submit the
        case.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <ac:image>
        <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-21-50.png" />
    </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Agent can see "Edit", "Cancel" and "Submit" buttons.</li>
    <li>In case of any soft blocks (SAP blocks or other), the 'Submit' button will be disabled and agent would be
        notified by a toast message about the presence of soft blocks.</li>
    <li>Then agent can edit the case again or continue and submit the case if no soft blocks are present.</li>
    <li>On click of the Submit button, the case is submitted with case status as 'Pending Approval' and agent is
        redirected to the 'Case Detail Page'.</li>
    <li>If agent clicks on Cancel then the case is saved with "Open, Unsubmitted" status and agent is redirected to the
        related 'Case Detail Page'.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="b99ec9e5-806e-401c-909a-c134071dd3cb" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note: Email Approval Scenario</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>For Exception Intake, every case must first be approved by an external approver to get 'RMA Authorized'.
            </li>
            <li>Scenarios:<ul>
                    <li>If total price overridden for line items is greater than 25k, then first the 'L3 Approver' needs
                        to approve the particular line items before the case is sent to the External approver.</li>
                    <li>If the L3 approver declines the approval request, then Case status is set to 'Declined' and
                        external approval will not be triggered.</li>
                    <li>In case of price override less than 25k, on load of the 'View Summary page', the email of the
                        external approver is fetched from the 'Approval Matrix' by sending sold to CMF, remedy, return
                        reason, service type, distribution channel and sales org along with net credit price.</li>
                    <li>If Remedy is <strong>'Credit'</strong> and Return Reason is <strong>'Exception Return'</strong>,
                        on load of the 'View Summary page', the email of the external approver is fetched from the 'ILM
                        Approval Matrix' by sending sold to CMF, service type, approver source, Location Geography along
                        with valid 'From' and 'To' dates. <span
                            style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);">#this is controlled by custom
                            settings and the value inside has more return reasons</span>
                    </li>
                    <li>On click of the 'Submit' button, case status is set to 'Pending Approval' and email is sent to
                        the approver for approval.</li>
                    <li>If no approver record is found, agent is notified by an error toast message.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
