<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.13. ">Case Edit Flow</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>For RMA Authorized Cases</strong>, only RTC Address and RTC Contacts can be edited, and nothing else can
        be edited.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>For Open, Unsubmitted cases</strong>, we check SAP Blocks on Load when the Edit R4C button is clicked,
        and if any hard blocks exist or if any inactive records are part of the case, then it's a hard stop and Agents
        can't edit the case; else if no blocks and no inactive CMFs, Agent can edit all the Collection details as well
        as Line Items.
    </li>
    <li>The Default landing page for the line items is the Search/Upload Line Items Page; line items can be deleted by
        using the dropdown or by unselecting the line items, and in the database the line items status gets set to
        Deleted.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    <u>Cancel Line Items:</u>
</p>
<ul>
    <li>In the Edit Case tab, we have an additional column 'Line items status' where the agent can select to delete line
        items.</li>
    <li>If the agent selects 'delete', then he will be shown a prompt to confirm if he really wants to delete the line
        item.</li>
    <li>Agent can also unselect the line items which will have the same functionality as selecting 'Delete' status.</li>
    <li>
        <strong>For Pending Approval Cases</strong>, only RTC Address and RTC Contact fields can be edited;
        additionally, if Freight Type is IMF, Collection Date can also be edited.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>RTC/Collection, Date Edit scenarios</strong>: After clicking on the Edit button, agent can edit the
        RTC/Collection address and Date fields for the RMA Authorised cases.
    </li>
</ul>
