<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="ffccc74a-4ecb-4b74-84b8-381a678190cd" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Notes in Edit Scenario</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>For Exception Intake, when agent edits the case, he cannot increase the Return Quantity of any line
                item. He is only allowed to decrease it. In case the agent increases the Return Quantity of any line
                item, the 'Save' button is disabled and the agent is notified by an error message.</li>
            <li>In Edit Case scenario, for any line item, if the earlier entitlement check date is on the same day, we
                will not be doing the Entitlement check for that Line item again and we use earlier data; but if any new
                line items are added, then the Entitlement check API callout will happen for the newly added Line Items.
            </li>
            <li>If the case is being edited and the earlier line items have gone beyond the Credit Price Validation step
                and the earlier detected credit price is on the same day, then the credit price validation API call is
                bypassed for existing line items.</li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
